that would be you?

265
00:31:29.060 --> 00:31:30.650
Who else?

266
00:31:33.030 --> 00:31:34.930
Since when do you babysit tourists?

267
00:31:35.000 --> 00:31:36.930
It's a small embassy. We all help out.

268
00:31:37.100 --> 00:31:40.000
Look. these people need you. all right?

269
00:31:40.140 --> 00:31:42.570
The cops have nothing.
The raids do nothing.

270
00:31:42.640 --> 00:31:44.800
The real bad guys are protected.

271
00:31:45.110 --> 00:31:46.630
Your friend. the inspector?

272
00:31:46.710 --> 00:31:49.230
Well. let's just say he's got the finesse
of a bull in a china shop.

273
00:31:49.310 --> 00:31:50.570
Why don't you dig around?

274
00:31:51.050 --> 00:31:53.740
I'm a paper pusher with security clearance.

275
00:31:53.820 --> 00:31:57.120
I don't have your flexibility
or your skill set.

276
00:31:58.390 --> 00:32:00.650
Sorry. I can't. You know I can't.

277
00:32:00.720 --> 00:32:02.690
The girl is 14 years old.

278
00:32:02.960 --> 00:32:05.290
It's been over 24 hours.

279
00:32:05.660 --> 00:32:08.360
Dad. she's running out of time.

280
00:32:08.430 --> 00:32:10.020
She needs you. all right?

281
00:32:10.430 --> 00:32:12.660
- Plus. you need this.
- I can't!

282
00:32:13.540 --> 00:32:16.900
- Stay out of it.
- Do you enjoy seeing dead people?

283
00:32:17.610 --> 00:32:20.080
Do you? Do you enjoy seeing dead people?

284
00:32:20.640 --> 00:32:24.270
Hey. if I want bullshit psychology.
I'll call your mother.

285
00:32:25.680 --> 00:32:29.550
Well. if you don't help people anymore.
then all you are is a goddamn butcher.

286
00:32:30.350 --> 00:32:32.450
Your grandpa was a butcher.

287
00:32:33.590 --> 00:32:35.220
People need meat.

288
00:35:02.140 --> 00:35:05.230
This girl. have you seen her?
She's my daughter.

289
00:35:08.410 --> 00:35:09.970
My name is the right money.

290
00:35:34.500 --> 00:35:35.600
You've seen her?

291
00:35:40.180 --> 00:35:41.340
Thank you.

292
00:36:40.440 --> 00:36:42.530
Hey. sweetie. you want to buy me a drink?

293
00:36:44.270 --> 00:36:47.440
- No. thanks.
- Okay.

294
00:36:50.910 --> 00:36:52.310
Excuse me.

295
00:36:52.520 --> 00:36:53.570
Yes?

296
00:36:55.450 --> 00:36:58.110
This girl. have you seen her?

297
00:36:59.560 --> 00:37:00.580
Nope.

298
00:37:01.620 --> 00:37:04.420
Are you sure? Take a better look.

299
00:37:06.200 --> 00:37:07.990
The woman outside. the gypsy lady...

300
00:37:08.130 --> 00:37:09.830
No such thing as gypsy lady.

301
00:37:09.930 --> 00:37:11.330
They're all whores.

302
00:37:11.500 --> 00:37:14.400
- And thieves.
- Thieving whores.

303
00:37:17.770 --> 00:37:18.970
Sorry. I did not see her.

304
00:37:20.210 --> 00:37:23.650
Why would the lady outside
say that she saw her?

305
00:37:23.750 --> 00:37:27.200
Mister. that gypsy witch outside
has not been sober in three years.

306
00:37:28.550 --> 00:37:32.110
Also. it's an easy mistake to make.
They all blondes here.

307
00:37:32.890 --> 00:37:35.410
You see? Golden girls.

308
00:37:36.390 --> 00:37:38.620
That's what we call the place.

309
00:37:46.070 --> 00:37:49.060
Have you seen her anywhere around here?

310
00:37:51.870 --> 00:37:55.040
Wow. She is... How you say...

311
00:37:56.150 --> 00:37:57.270
Hot.

312
00:37:58.510 --> 00:37:59.570
Hot.

313
00:38:01.020 --> 00:38:02.350
She's my daughter.

314
00:38:02.990 --> 00:38:05.680
Why you let her come to a place like this?

315
00:38:05.760 --> 00:38:09.250
I tell you. American economy. very bad.

316
00:38:11.160 --> 00:38:13.720
Sending kids to make extra money.

317
00:38:14.530 --> 00:38:18.060
If your daughter come here.
you're not very good father.

318
00:38:22.840 --> 00:38:24.240
What'd you say to me?

319
00:38:27.940 --> 00:38:29.970
Come on. partner. time to go.

320
00:40:45.650 --> 00:40:47.050
Come on. I got you.

321
00:41:12.610 --> 00:41:14.240
How'd you find me?

322
00:41:15.950 --> 00:41:18.540
Finding people. it's what I do.

323
00:41:19.420 --> 00:41:21.010
Plus. it wasn't hard.

324
00:41:21.080 --> 00:41:24.990
Not many Americans running around clubs.
pissing people off.

325
00:41:25.050 --> 00:41:26.520
All right. so now you want to help?

326
00:41:31.060 --> 00:41:32.550
Are you sober?

327
00:41:34.760 --> 00:41:36.990
Until I find your daughter.
Then. we'll see.

328
00:41:39.370 --> 00:41:41.430
Why'd you change your mind?

329
00:41:42.400 --> 00:41:44.340
It's the right thing to do.

330
00:41:49.410 --> 00:41:51.110
One more thing. I work alone.

331
00:41:51.280 --> 00:41:53.180
You're a good fighter...

332
00:41:53.450 --> 00:41:54.920
But you make lots of noise.

333
00:41:55.050 --> 00:41:56.880
I can see you coming miles away.

334
00:41:57.650 --> 00:41:59.480
What. and they can't see you?

335
00:42:00.620 --> 00:42:02.280
They never do.

336
00:42:08.760 --> 00:42:09.960
We have a lead.

337
00:42:10.770 --> 00:42:13.830
Your daughter was most likely
taken out of the hotel in the ambulance

338
00:42:13.970 --> 00:42:17.770
that you saw when you
first ran down looking for her.

339
00:42:17.840 --> 00:42:19.470
They said it was an older lady.

340
00:42:19.580 --> 00:42:21.270
They were either mistaken.

341
00:42:21.580 --> 00:42:25.240
or the kidnappers dyed your daughter's hair

342
00:42:25.310 --> 00:42:27.750
when they drugged her unconscious.

343
00:42:28.480 --> 00:42:29.880
We now know that

344
00:42:29.950 --> 00:42:33.750
the guest listed as calling the ambulance
never actually stayed at the hotel.

345
00:42:34.290 --> 00:42:36.260
And you're just figuring this out now?

346
00:42:37.790 --> 00:42:39.780
It's been two days!

347
00:42:40.130 --> 00:42:42.860
Mrs. Fayden. I share your frustration.

348
00:42:43.100 --> 00:42:44.360
Do you?

349
00:42:45.900 --> 00:42:49.000
Becky could be halfway
across the world by now.

350
00:42:50.040 --> 00:42:52.030
And no one's asked for a ransom.

351
00:42:52.210 --> 00:42:57.040
So the chances of this being a trafficking
case are 80 to 90% more likely!

352
00:42:57.210 --> 00:43:00.880
Mrs. Fayden. the statistics on
the internet. they are not...

353
00:43:00.950 --> 00:43:06.180
The recovery rate for kidnapped children
after 24 hours drops to 46%!

354
00:43:07.220 --> 00:43:09.090
That's less than half!

355
00:43:10.390 --> 00:43:13.260
Constantin. give us a moment.

356
00:43:23.540 --> 00:43:25.300
Mr. and Mrs. Fayden.

357
00:43:25.910 --> 00:43:28.840
let me. as you say. cut to the chase.

358
00:43:29.040 --> 00:43:31.980
I have learned you have hired
a private consultant.

359
00:43:32.850 --> 00:43:34.610
Mr. Samson Gaul.

360
00:43:36.690 --> 00:43:39.050
At this point. we can use
all the help we can get.

361
00:43:40.320 --> 00:43:44.090
- I would not place your trust in this man.
- Why?

362
00:43:44.530 --> 00:43:47.430
Because he might actually get some results?

363
00:43:48.200 --> 00:43:49.630
Make you look bad?

364
00:43:49.830 --> 00:43:51.700
He is not a detective.

365
00:43:52.530 --> 00:43:55.830
He is an ex-mercenary. A hired killer.

366
00:43:56.410 --> 00:43:59.400
Do you really want such a man
working for you?

367
00:43:59.880 --> 00:44:03.470
I'll hire the goddamn devil himself
if it gets my daughter back.

368
00:44:07.020 --> 00:44:10.420
I hope you do not come
to regret your decision.

369
00:44:10.750 --> 00:44:14.920
His last recovery effort resulted
in the deaths of four girls.

370
00:44:15.760 --> 00:44:18.090
Two the same age as Becky.

371
00:44:18.630 --> 00:44:19.990
Two younger.

372
00:44:21.930 --> 00:44:25.990
Although we may not be moving
as quickly as you imagine we should.

373
00:44:26.440 --> 00:44:28.060
I want you to know.

374
00:44:28.140 --> 00:44:32.700
it is my number one priority
to get your daughter back to you safely.

375
00:44:36.510 --> 00:44:38.480
I just thought you should
have all the facts.

376
00:44:41.020 --> 00:44:43.710
Well. we'll take that under advisement.

377
00:44:44.820 --> 00:44:46.290
I understand.

378
00:44:47.390 --> 00:44:51.020
I will send someone to take you home.
I will call you later.

379
00:45:26.300 --> 00:45:28.860
- Good evening.
- It's a little late for delivery.

380
00:45:29.030 --> 00:45:31.860
I know. but the overtime is worth it.

381
00:45:32.570 --> 00:45:33.590
Please.

382
00:45:37.010 --> 00:45:38.340
Sign here.

383
00:46:19.450 --> 00:46:21.420
Guys. Keep your eyes open.

384
00:46:21.520 --> 00:46:24.180
Something's up with the monitors.

385
00:46:34.100 --> 00:46:35.090
Stop!

386
00:46:36.870 --> 00:46:38.130
Stop! Stop!

387
00:47:04.490 --> 00:47:05.960
Who's guarding the back?

388
00:47:13.670 --> 00:47:14.690
Up.

389
00:47:22.640 --> 00:47:24.310
What the fuck?

390
00:47:24.410 --> 00:47:26.510
- Boss. come on. let's get you to the vault.
- Who are they?

391
00:47:26.580 --> 00:47:29.180
I don't know. but we can't
take any chances. Come on!

392
00:48:10.930 --> 00:48:14.380
It's the fucking Russians! Gotta be.
Get more guys over here.

393
00:48:14.460 --> 00:48:15.830
Done.

394
00:48:42.420 --> 00:48:44.950
You may not feel it yet. but you will soon.

395
00:48:49.500 --> 00:48:54.330
It's a reminder of the most important
person in your life as of right now.

396
00:48:55.500 --> 00:48:57.340
You know who I am?

397
00:48:57.840 --> 00:49:01.330
That's why I'm here.
I want the man in charge.

398
00:49:07.180 --> 00:49:08.620
Where is she?

399
00:49:09.320 --> 00:49:10.840
American girl.

400
00:49:11.620 --> 00:49:14.590
- Not my thing.
- Then who?

401
00:49:15.260 --> 00:49:16.720
I don't know.

402
00:49:17.530 --> 00:49:21.090
Never touch Americans. Bad for business.

403
00:49:21.300 --> 00:49:25.200
Fucking cops raiding my clubs for days now.

404
00:49:25.770 --> 00:49:26.830
Competition.

405
00:49:27.040 --> 00:49:29.940
- Who wants to hurt you?
- Russians.

406
00:49:30.270 --> 00:49:31.760
Always trying to move in.

407
00:49:31.940 --> 00:49:35.770
The only reason you're alive
is because you have a job to do.

408
00:49:36.140 --> 00:49:38.700
- I told you...
- Shut up.

409
00:49:39.950 --> 00:49:41.580
You run the city.

410
00:49:42.250 --> 00:49:45.050
You find this girl as quickly as possible.

411
00:49:45.150 --> 00:49:48.550
And you bring her back to her parents
by this time tomorrow.

412
00:49:51.290 --> 00:49:56.130
If not. I'll come back here
and I'll carve out your eyes one by one.

413
00:49:57.070 --> 00:49:58.460
Am I clear?

414
00:50:00.170 --> 00:50:01.260
Yeah.

415
00:50:30.000 --> 00:50:32.630
Your passport is proof of who you are.

416
00:50:34.840 --> 00:50:35.960
You're no one now.

417
00:50:39.470 --> 00:50:42.640
I pay good money for you.
so now you work for me.

418
00:50:44.250 --> 00:50:45.470
Take it off.

419
00:50:49.050 --> 00:50:50.280
Everything.

420
00:51:01.030 --> 00:51:02.430
Is there a problem?

421
00:51:03.730 --> 00:51:05.500
Please. I can't.

422
00:51:16.240 --> 00:51:18.300
The next time you don't
do what you're told.

423
00:51:19.920 --> 00:51:21.180
I take this knife...

424
00:51:40.240 --> 00:51:41.930
You know the drill.

425
00:51:42.000 --> 00:51:44.490
Test them out and put them to work.

426
00:51:50.850 --> 00:51:51.870
Da?

427
00:51:51.950 --> 00:51:56.150
Your retard cousin is drawing too much heat.
Shut him down.

428
00:51:56.220 --> 00:51:58.380
The Al Khabiri thing
could be worth millions.

429
00:51:58.690 --> 00:52:02.590
I've made up my mind.
It's not worth the risk.

430
00:52:03.530 --> 00:52:06.790
Shut it down or I'll find
someone else who will.

431
00:52:27.120 --> 00:52:28.280
Hello?

432
00:52:28.680 --> 00:52:31.620
It's me. I need a GPS
trace on a cell phone.

433
00:52:32.620 --> 00:52:34.850
That's not easy. I'll have to go into work.

434
00:52:34.920 --> 00:52:37.920
Okay. get moving
and I'll text you the number.

435
00:52:38.060 --> 00:52:43.160
I'll also need any information
on someone or something called Al Khabiri.

436
00:52:44.630 --> 00:52:46.790
Fine. Anything else. Dad?

437
00:52:46.900 --> 00:52:49.670
You want me back? This is me back.

438
00:53:40.460 --> 00:53:41.890
What's going on?

439
00:53:44.030 --> 00:53:45.820
Come on. what's going on?

440
00:53:48.130 --> 00:53:51.190
Change of plans. we're shutting down.

441
00:53:51.530 --> 00:53:52.630
What?

442
00:53:53.370 --> 00:53:56.530
- Bogdanov wants out.
- No! The money's too big.

443
00:53:56.740 --> 00:53:59.400
That old fuck's just too rich and scared
to follow through.

444
00:54:01.410 --> 00:54:03.640
- I see who's got the balls around here.
- Fuck off!

445
00:54:03.710 --> 00:54:06.200
- You shut the fuck up.
- Who needs Bogdanov?

446
00:54:06.510 --> 00:54:10.310
We've got the merchandise.
A virgin. American blonde.

447
00:54:10.490 --> 00:54:12.510
We have exactly what they wanted.

448
00:54:15.420 --> 00:54:17.320
You see this? It's our ticket.

449
00:54:17.760 --> 00:54:21.290
We call the guy. We make our own deal.

450
00:54:21.360 --> 00:54:22.730
Shut up.

451
00:54:22.800 --> 00:54:24.770
Do you want to be a lackey
for the rest of your life.

452
00:54:24.830 --> 00:54:27.060
or are you ready to make some real money?

453
00:54:35.940 --> 00:54:37.070
Tell you one thing. cousin.

454
00:54:38.880 --> 00:54:40.610
you sure got yourself a live one.

455
00:54:50.460 --> 00:54:52.090
Stop. stop. stop!

456
00:54:55.600 --> 00:54:58.620
I told you. smart women are trouble.

457
00:54:59.730 --> 00:55:00.720
Please.

458
00:55:07.580 --> 00:55:09.870
Now what do I tell your mother?

459
00:55:56.190 --> 00:55:57.250
Hold.

460
00:56:08.000 --> 00:56:09.590
Let him through.

461
00:56:14.010 --> 00:56:17.440
- The girl?
- Well. see for yourself.

462
00:56:23.020 --> 00:56:26.420
One of Bogdanov's recruiters
and his sometime girlfriend.

463
00:56:32.560 --> 00:56:33.790
In here.

464
00:56:48.880 --> 00:56:50.710
Her face is gone. You sure it's her?

465
00:56:50.810 --> 00:56:53.580
We're checking the DNA samples
from the parents.

466
00:57:01.790 --> 00:57:04.090
It's Bogdanov. He shut it down.

467
00:57:04.860 --> 00:57:07.050
I heard him giving the order.

468
00:57:08.600 --> 00:57:11.000
And you did not think to call us?

469
00:57:11.470 --> 00:57:14.400
Of course not. Always the cowboy.

470
00:57:18.040 --> 00:57:20.560
Stick to what you know. butcher.

471
00:57:41.930 --> 00:57:44.630
Did the coordinates work? Was she here?

472
00:57:45.100 --> 00:57:46.230
Yeah.

473
00:58:07.720 --> 00:58:10.420
I just don't understand.

474
00:58:12.230 --> 00:58:13.220
Why would they...

475
00:58:16.060 --> 00:58:18.970
I mean. if it is her...

476
00:58:21.170 --> 00:58:23.160
Why would they want to...

477
00:58:23.740 --> 00:58:25.430
it seems that whoever took her

478
00:58:25.570 --> 00:58:26.970
felt under pressure.

479
00:58:27.040 --> 00:58:29.870
Afraid that they're going to be found out.

480
00:58:31.680 --> 00:58:34.340
Someone pushed them too hard. I guess.

481
00:58:47.600 --> 00:58:49.150
I'm sorry.

482
00:58:49.430 --> 00:58:52.990
The DNA match is positive. It's her.

483
00:59:51.260 --> 00:59:53.690
It's not your fault. Dad.
It's not your fault.

484
00:59:55.400 --> 00:59:57.060
Come on. let's go.

485
01:00:33.600 --> 01:00:37.230
- You can go. I'll be fine.
- I think it's better if I stay.

486
01:00:38.270 --> 01:00:39.500
You put me up to this.

487
01:00:40.410 --> 01:00:42.100
You knew I was no good!

488
01:00:43.240 --> 01:00:44.580
A girl is dead now!

489
01:00:45.450 --> 01:00:46.710
It's your fault. too!

490
01:00:46.850 --> 01:00:48.710
It's not my fault.
It's not your fault either. Dad.

491
01:00:48.780 --> 01:00:50.510
Get away from here!

492
01:00:57.530 --> 01:00:59.120
Get the fuck outta here!

493
01:03:22.070 --> 01:03:25.330
A butcher with feelings. Who knew?

494
01:03:36.880 --> 01:03:38.040
Do it.

495
01:03:39.340 --> 01:03:42.370
- You will be doing me a favor.
- We're not here for favors.

496
01:03:44.380 --> 01:03:46.110
Here to punish you.

497
01:03:49.160 --> 01:03:50.520
Come to my home.

498
01:03:52.030 --> 01:03:53.260
You kill my men.

499
01:03:58.300 --> 01:04:01.330
You threaten me. Mutilate me.

500
01:04:10.580 --> 01:04:11.780
The DNA match is...

501
01:04:31.210 --> 01:04:32.900
You really do want to die.

502
01:05:08.180 --> 01:05:09.510
- You okay?
- Yeah.

503
01:05:12.050 --> 01:05:13.950
Whatcha doing here anyway?

504
01:05:14.890 --> 01:05:18.090
- I was worried about you.
- The girl.

505
01:05:44.620 --> 01:05:47.250
What is it? What's going on?

506
01:05:50.460 --> 01:05:52.760
- I need you to drive.
- To drive?

507
01:05:52.830 --> 01:05:54.600
- Let's go.
- Okay.

508
01:06:35.950 --> 01:06:38.680
- All right. please stay away from us.
- It's about your daughter.

509
01:06:39.420 --> 01:06:41.950
You're drunk. Get the fuck out of here!

510
01:06:42.290 --> 01:06:45.350
Hey. give him a chance. all right?
Listen to him. Please.

511
01:06:45.490 --> 01:06:49.120
Your daughter. she always
wear her bracelet on the right.

512
01:06:49.300 --> 01:06:50.290
What?

513
01:06:50.370 --> 01:06:52.960
Does Becky wear her bracelet
on her right hand?

514
01:06:53.500 --> 01:06:54.630
I think so.

515
01:06:55.200 --> 01:06:58.610
In all the photos.
her bracelet always on the right wrist.

516
01:06:59.040 --> 01:07:02.210
When they found her. it
was on the left wrist.

517
01:07:06.180 --> 01:07:10.520
It's a setup. It's all too neat.
Girls are nothing to them.

518
01:07:10.790 --> 01:07:14.160
They killed another blonde girl
and made her look like Becky.

519
01:07:14.290 --> 01:07:15.690
I think your daughter's not dead.

520
01:07:18.130 --> 01:07:20.530
What's the point?
Why would they fake her death?

521
01:07:20.640 --> 01:07:21.930
It's simple.

522
01:07:22.000 --> 01:07:25.130
You kidnap an American girl here.
you have too much heat.

523
01:07:25.410 --> 01:07:28.670
How do you stop people from looking.
but still profit from the girl?

